    <stitle>FULL POWER HYDRAULIC ABS BRAKE SYSTEM - GENERAL DESCRIPTION - WARNING INDICATORS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl04051205" graphiccount="1">
        <title>WARNING INDICATORS</title>
        <para>Indicators located in the Electronic Gauge Cluster (EGC), are used to display the status of the brake
            system. Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0405101">FIGURE 1</hotlnk>. Some of the indicators identify conditions that may require
            service. In addition to the warning indicators, a buzzer is sounded for certain conditions. In the event
            that a lit indicator is the result of a malfunction, diagnostic codes identifying the source of the
            malfunction will be stored in the ECU memory. Retrieval of the diagnostic codes is explained in the
            diagnostic section of this manual. Although the following table lists possible malfunctions for each warning
            indicator, some malfunctions will result in more than one indicator being lit.
        </para>
        <table id="t0405101" tblwidth="pg-wide">
            <title>Warning Indicators</title>
            <tgroup cols="4">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.31*"/>
                <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="0.39*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.31*"/>
                <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.55*"/>
                <spanspec namest="COLSPEC0" nameend="col2" spanname="SPAN3"/>
                <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="COLSPEC0" spanname="SPAN2"/>
                <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col2" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1" valign="bottom" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">INDICATOR</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry valign="bottom" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SYSTEM CONDITION BEING INDICATED</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN2">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">BRAKE</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">(RED)</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- SOLID ON</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Half system failure.</emph>
                                A sensor in the HCU has detected low pressure (&#60;1550 psi) in the accumulator for
                                either the front or rear brake circuit. Warning buzzer is also sounded.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- FLASHING</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Full system failure.</emph>
                                A sensor in the HCU has detected low pressure (&#60;1550 psi) in the accumulators for
                                both the front and rear brake circuits. Warning buzzer is also sounded. In addition,
                                once vehicle speed drops below 25 mph, engine limiting will limit the vehicle speed to
                                25 mph or less.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- OFF</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>System pressures are in normal range.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN2">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">BRAKE FLUID</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">(RED)</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- SOLID ON</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Low brake fluid level detected in the Master Cylinder reservoir.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- OFF</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Brake fluid level detected in the Master Cylinder reservoir is at or above MIN.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN2">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ABS</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">(AMBER)</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- SOLID ON</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>An ABS related fault has been detected by the ECU.</para>
                            <para>-OR-</para>
                            <para>Communications between the ECU and the Body Controller/EGC have been lost.</para>
                            <para>-OR-</para>
                            <para>The ECU is not receiving power.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- OFF</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>No ABS related faults have been detected by the ECU.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN2">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TRAC CTRL</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">(GREEN)</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(Vehicles equipped with optional ATC)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- SOLID ON</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>The TRAC CTRL indicator will be continuously lit whenever:</para>
                            <para>A traction control related fault has been detected.</para>
                            <para>- OR -</para>
                            <para>The ATC system is operating correctly, and an ATC event is occurring.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- FLASHING</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>The TRAC CTRL indicator will be flashing whenever the Mud and Snow mode has been
                                selected using the traction control switch (switch indicator lit).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- OFF</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>The ATC system is operating correctly, the Mud and Snow mode has not been selected,
                                and the vehicle is not experiencing an ATC event.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN2">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">BRAKE</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Some vehicles have an additional BRAKE indicator located in one of the indicator
                                quadrants below the speedometer and tach. The specific location of this indicator may
                                vary.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- SOLID ON</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Low brake fluid level detected in the Master Cylinder reservoir.</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">OR</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Half system failure. A sensor in the HCU has detected low pressure (&#60;1550 psi) in
                                the accumulator for either the front or rear brake circuit. Warning buzzer is also
                                sounded.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- FLASHING</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Full system failure. A sensor in the HCU has detected low pressure (&#60;1550 psi) in
                                the accumulators for both the front and rear brake circuits. Warning buzzer is also
                                sounded.
                            </para>
                            <para>Once vehicle speed drops below 25 mph, engine limiting will limit the vehicle speed to
                                25 mph or less.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry></entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN3">
                            <para>- OFF</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>System pressures are in normal range, and the brake fluid level detected in the Master
                                Cylinder reservoir is at or above MIN.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
